I have plenty of in-progress first drafts that need time and serious work.
An idea will only take you so far. Knowing the mechanics of how a story is constructed gets you a bit further.
In my case, some things need a scene-by-scene breakdown after the first draft. I'm not a tabletop gamer so my improv skills are limited. Instead, I track character arcs, sensory details, and the physical/mental/emotional toll for each new scene.
I can only hope that the effort I put into my work pays off.

As for the not good enough? Get over it. People like to do the fun parts, not the hard work. No matter how naturally good you are at something, it takes grit to go from conception to end product. That fun bit is the cherry at the end.
